	voiceIntroHtml={`Nine Bible verses for widows and widowers in the Father's Heart Bible™ — each one a word from your Father into the place that hurts most. Tap any reference to read and listen free.`}
	verses={[
		{ ref: `Psalm 68:5`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 68, text: `A father to the fatherless, a defender of widows, is your Father in His holy dwelling.`, note: `Of all His titles, He chose this one for you — your defender, the One who stands up for the widow.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 54:5`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 54, text: `For your Maker is your husband — the Lord of hosts is His name; the Holy One is your Redeemer, the God of all the earth.`, note: `The covering you lost, He promises to be Himself — your Maker steps into the empty place.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 34:18`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 34, text: `Your Father is near to the brokenhearted and saves those who are crushed in spirit.`, note: `Grief does not push Him away — it is exactly where He draws closest.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 147:3`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 147, text: `He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds.`, note: `He does not rush your healing or shame your tears — He tends the wound gently, in His time.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 68:6`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 68, text: `Your Father sets the lonely in families; He leads out the prisoners to prosperity.`, note: `He sees the silent house, and He is the God who places the lonely back among the loved.` },
		{ ref: `Deuteronomy 10:18`, slug: `deuteronomy`, ch: 10, text: `He executes justice for the fatherless and the widow, and He loves the stranger, giving them food and clothing.`, note: `Your provision is not an afterthought to Him — caring for the widow is something He does Himself.` },
		{ ref: `Lamentations 3:22-23`, slug: `lamentations`, ch: 3, text: `The steadfast love of your Father never ceases; His mercies never come to an end — they are new every morning; great is His faithfulness.`, note: `Even the mornings that feel impossible carry a fresh mercy with your name on it.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 146:9`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 146, text: `Your Father watches over the sojourner; He upholds the widow and the fatherless, but the way of the wicked He brings to ruin.`, note: `When you feel most unprotected, He names Himself the One who upholds you.` },
		{ ref: `Revelation 21:4`, slug: `revelation`, ch: 21, text: `Your Father will wipe away every tear from their eyes, and death shall be no more, neither shall there be mourning, nor crying, nor pain anymore.`, note: `This separation is not the final word — the day is coming when He wipes away the last tear Himself.` },
