	offersHeading={`What "our Father" offers the widow and widower`}
	offersIntroHtml={`Grief takes so much. Here is what your Father gives — freely, because you are still His, and held more closely now than ever.`}
	offersBlocks={[
		{ heading: `A defender who stands up for you`, bodyHtml: `When you feel unprotected and unseen, your Father names Himself the <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/68" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">protector of the widow</a> — the One who stands up for the person who has lost their covering.` },
		{ heading: `Nearness in the brokenhearted hours`, bodyHtml: `He does not keep His distance from your grief. Scripture says your Father is <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/34" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">near to the brokenhearted</a> and saves those crushed in spirit — closest in the moments you feel most alone.` },
		{ heading: `Provision when the future feels uncertain`, bodyHtml: `He calls caring for the widow His own work: your Father <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/deuteronomy/10" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">executes justice and provides</a> for the widow Himself. Your needs are not invisible to Him.` },
		{ heading: `A hope that outlasts the grave`, bodyHtml: `This goodbye is not the end of the story. One day your Father will <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/revelation/21" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">wipe away every tear</a>, and death will be no more — a reunion no loss can cancel.` },
	]}
