	voicesHeading={`The Father's heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`There is no grief too heavy for the Father to hold with you. The truth beneath every verse here — that God is, before anything else, a Father to the fatherless and a defender of widows — is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Andrew Murray, George MacDonald, and Charles Spurgeon (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>There may be days the verses feel like words on a page and the comfort seems far off. That's allowed. Grief comes in waves, and faith doesn't mean feeling fine. Even when you can't feel it, every line of Scripture you take in is your Father drawing near — a mercy that is new again every single morning, including this one.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I see you. I see the empty chair and the half-set table, the nights that feel endless and the mornings you wake before you remember. I have not looked away from your grief, and I have not forgotten you. I am near to the brokenhearted — nearer now than you can feel — and I am keeping every tear you cry.</p><p>You are not on your own, even when the house is quiet and the calls have stopped. I am the defender of the widow; I will be the covering you have lost. Bring Me your fears about the future, your loneliness, the love that has nowhere to go — bring it all to Me. You are still Mine, deeply and completely, and one day I will wipe away the last tear with My own hand. Until then, I am here. I am your Father, and I am staying."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for widows and widowers`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You for these widows and widowers — for every heart that has loved deeply and is grieving the one they lost. You call Yourself the Father to the fatherless and the defender of the widow, and so we ask You to be exactly that for them now. You see the empty chair and the silent house, the side of the bed no one fills, the long evenings no one else notices. Draw near, Lord — as near as Your Word promises You are to the brokenhearted.</p><p>Comfort them in their grief; let them mourn without shame and heal without hurry. Quiet their fears about the future — provide for them, defend them, and meet the needs that keep them awake. Be their companion in the loneliness, their protection in every vulnerable place, and a steady presence on the days that feel impossible. Set the lonely in families, Father; surround them with people who stay.</p><p>Above all, let them know they are still deeply Yours and have never for one moment been forgotten — that You keep count of their tossing and store every tear, and that the day is coming when You will wipe them all away. Hold them close until then, and be the home their hearts are aching for.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
