	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for widows?`, answer: `Psalm 68:5 (Father of the fatherless and protector of widows), Isaiah 54:5 (your Maker is your husband), Psalm 34:18 (near to the brokenhearted), Psalm 147:3 (He heals the brokenhearted), Deuteronomy 10:18 (He provides for the widow), Lamentations 3:22-23 (mercies new every morning), and Revelation 21:4 (He will wipe away every tear) speak directly to widows and widowers. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about widows?`, answer: `The Bible holds the widow especially close to God's heart. Psalm 68:5 calls God the "Father of the fatherless and protector of widows," and James 1:27 says caring for widows is religion that is pure before God. Far from being overlooked, the widow is named again and again as someone God personally defends, provides for, and draws near to. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet that God as a Father — free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What are Bible verses for comfort after losing a spouse?`, answer: `When the loss is fresh, Psalm 34:18 (the Lord is near to the brokenhearted), Psalm 147:3 (He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds), Lamentations 3:22-23 (His mercies are new every morning), and Revelation 21:4 (He will wipe away every tear) offer real comfort — not by rushing your grief, but by promising you are not alone in it. The Father's Heart Bible™ lets you read or listen to these free, in a voice that reveals God as a Father near to you.` },
		{ question: `Does God care for widows and widowers?`, answer: `Yes — deeply and specifically. Of all the ways God describes Himself, He chose "protector of widows" (Psalm 68:5), and Deuteronomy 10:18 says He executes justice and provides for the widow Himself. Isaiah 54:5 even promises, "Your Maker is your husband." Whether you are a widow or a widower, Scripture is clear: you have not slipped from God's notice — you have moved nearer to His heart.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio for those who are grieving?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book. For the lonely, sleepless hours, the audio means you can simply let His Word be read over you in the quiet of the house.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for widows?`, answer: `It is the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — including as the defender and provider of the widow. For someone grieving a spouse, that changes everything: instead of reading rules, you meet the One who calls Himself the protector of the widow and promises to be the covering you have lost. You come to the Bible as a beloved, defended child — not someone left on their own.` },
		{ question: `How can I start reading the Bible after losing my spouse?`, answer: `Start gently and start free. Open fathersheartbible.com/read, and rather than a long reading plan, begin with a single Psalm — Psalm 34, Psalm 68, or Psalm 147 — and let the audio read it over you. A verse a day is enough. Our how-to-pray guide and verses-by-topic pages can help you find words for grief when your own won't come.` },
	]}
